	   <tr><td colspan=2>I wouldn't say that rogues can't solo...I'd just say that it's a bit expensive...and sometimes unwise...<br>...I can still solo some mobs, not to mny, but some, like the dire wolves in GD, anywhere from high blue, to green.  I can solo them without poison sometimes, but I usually use it to be on the safe side...<br>...though its all situational, like take Kerosh Blackhand for example, he's a named bandit in the Feild of Bone, in the marauder caves.  Blue to me, around lvl 35 or so, in a straight out fight, he'd whomp me fast...I know, it's happend.<br>The last time I battled this foe, I was partnered with a friend of mine, 30th iksar monk, I used a Paralyze Poison III, which dropeds said mobs atk about 50%. I really turned this guy into a wuss, it was like fighting a lesser charbone or something, hehe, he went down fast.<br>The two of us did it again the next time he spawned, I used the same poison, though it wore off almost as soon as I tagged him width it, so monkey beat on him while I reapplied, and we whomped him once again...<br><br>So it's not that rogues CAN'T solo, its just that it seems to be safer not to try sometimes, take both those fights with Kerosh, had my friend not been there...First fight, I might have won, being as the poison took, and lasted the whole fight...Second Fight, he'da tore me apart right quick, being as the poison wore off right away...<br><br>Oh well, 'till next time, I remain me...<br><br>Gwildor, 41st Dwarven Rogue -Laramie Circle-<br>Orkko, 22nd Ogre Shaman -Laramie Circle-<br>Ekkimus, 17th Iksar Necromancer -Lifekeepers-<br><br>BRELL ! ! !<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
